 A three-year-old child who strayed from his grandmother's house is feared to have drowned. Police in Embu and the family are searching for him. One of David Roy Nyagah's shoes was found on the banks of River Kirii in Kibugu, Embu North sub-county. His father, David Kariuki Njue, reported the boy's disappearance at Kibugu Police Station on Monday. He had been in his grandmotherâ€™s house at Kithiria Village, Gicherori. Kirii River is swollen following heavy rains in the county. Njue said the grandmother and other family members unsuccessfully searched for Nyagah in the compound and the neighbourhood. 